Phone: ||Hotel was small, clean with a nice shared pool to lounge by. We enjoyed that it it's only few rooms, you get to meet everyone from their staff and know them personally. |They have free boat to inside ekas so even if you're not doing camp/having lesson with them, you can still go out for surf on your own easily. The boat is 5-10min walk from hotel.  |Food was good, lots of options - both indonesian and western - and they were able to cater for gluten free - just make sure to double check the ingredients or ask the owners Dave and Melissa to help (they're super friendly and make sure you have great stay and enjoy yourself).||Surf camp:||Surf camp was well organised, we only had one afternoon where it was super windy and not good conditions for surfing, otherwise it was very consistent and we had opportunity to try different breaks. I really enjoyed the lesson set up of having 1 surf guide per 2 people in the water, and then surf coach who sits on the side and sees you actually surf and give you guidance after every wave. Also being so close to Ekas meant we could be there before all boats from Kuta arrive ;-)|The photo and video surf analysis was also very useful and I appreciated all the coaching from Ewan (surf coach). The surf guides (Adir and Ahir) were also great!|Camps are 4 people only, we had quite a mix of skills and they really did they best to ensure everyone is getting value and has the right conditions to improve their skills.||Activities:||We did the snorkeling tour. Snorkeling was actually amazing, the reef was super vibrant and lots of fish. We visited 3 snorkeling spots and had pre-packed lunch to eat on the beach. ||Downsides:||The only downside, especially coming from Western Australia, was that there was rubbish in the water in some spots - but that's down to winds, current, end of wet season etc - not much the hotel/staff can do about! They actually even did beach cleaning at some point during the week which I thought was a great initiative. And we also visited spots were water was absolutely crystal clear!
